WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.480
[Amit Varma]: Many of my friends tell me that I'm a young man, but I'm afraid all these friends are

00:00:08.480 --> 00:00:09.480
[Amit Varma]: older than me.

00:00:09.480 --> 00:00:14.440
[Amit Varma]: I'm in my late 40s, and when you get here, you realize how fast time passes.

00:00:14.440 --> 00:00:18.480
[Amit Varma]: It seems like just yesterday that I was feeling the oppressive pressures of adulthood and

00:00:18.480 --> 00:00:19.480
[Amit Varma]: 30.

00:00:19.480 --> 00:00:22.080
[Amit Varma]: And boom, blink a few times, years have passed.

00:00:22.080 --> 00:00:24.020
[Amit Varma]: The scarcity of time becomes real.

00:00:24.020 --> 00:00:27.520
[Amit Varma]: And I guess one way of dealing with this is a modern way of living.

00:00:27.520 --> 00:00:31.400
[Amit Varma]: Do everything fast, fast, fast, throw yourself into the world.

00:00:31.400 --> 00:00:35.480
[Amit Varma]: Spend every waking moment doing something, even if it is only on your smartphone.

00:00:35.480 --> 00:00:38.080
[Amit Varma]: Life is always moving, but it doesn't go anywhere.

00:00:38.080 --> 00:00:39.080
[Amit Varma]: It is shallow.

00:00:39.080 --> 00:00:44.100
[Amit Varma]: I'm not berating others as much as I am lamenting my own choices and the weakness of character

00:00:44.100 --> 00:00:46.160
[Amit Varma]: that has stopped me from breaking out of this.

00:00:46.160 --> 00:00:47.920
[Amit Varma]: I want to live a slow life.

00:00:47.920 --> 00:00:52.080
[Amit Varma]: I want to have long conversations, sit with friends without the pressure of performing

00:00:52.080 --> 00:00:53.080
[Amit Varma]: for the world.

00:00:53.080 --> 00:00:57.040
[Amit Varma]: I want to go out, look at the world instead of being lost in my own head.

00:00:57.040 --> 00:00:58.400
[Amit Varma]: How can we learn to do this?

00:00:58.400 --> 00:01:04.380
[Amit Varma]: How can we stop throwing ourselves into the chaos around us, but just sit back and observe?

00:01:04.380 --> 00:01:06.840
[Amit Varma]: How do we give ourselves a space to reflect?

00:01:06.840 --> 00:01:08.920
[Amit Varma]: One way of doing so is to write.

00:01:08.920 --> 00:01:13.240
[Amit Varma]: If you build a habit of writing, then when you write, you withdraw into a quiet space

00:01:13.240 --> 00:01:16.140
[Amit Varma]: where life slows down and even becomes clearer.

00:01:16.140 --> 00:01:19.120
[Amit Varma]: You examine your own thoughts and perhaps even form them.

00:01:19.120 --> 00:01:22.600
[Amit Varma]: Because by writing every day, you don't just see the world a little better.

00:01:22.600 --> 00:01:25.120
[Amit Varma]: You also shape your own self.

00:01:25.120 --> 00:01:45.000
[Amit Varma]: And maybe that's the best way to fight against a relentless march of time.

00:01:45.000 --> 00:01:46.000
[Amit Varma]: The Scene and the Unseen.

